# Normalize all text files to LF in the working tree on every platform. Without
# this, Windows checkouts default to CRLF and `cargo fmt --check` fails against
# rustfmt's `newline_style = "Unix"`, and shell scripts break on a CRLF shebang.
* text=auto eol=lf

# The vendored screenshot font is binary: never apply EOL/text munging to it.
# Any byte change would alter the font freeze embeds into every SVG, silently
# drifting the screencomp baseline on the next capture.
*.ttf binary

# Generated terminal-screenshot SVGs are LF text (freeze emits LF); pin it so a
# Windows checkout cannot rewrite them to CRLF and diverge from the baseline.
*.svg text eol=lf
